# Frank Media - Configuration Guide

## Environment Variables

### Backend (.env)

```env
# Server Configuration
PORT=4000
NODE_ENV=development

# Admin Authentication
ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123

# Stripe (Optional - for production payments)
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...

# CORS
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173,http://localhost:3000

# Payment Mode
PAYMENT_MODE=mock  # Set to "stripe" for production

# PostgreSQL Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/frank_media
DATABASE_SSL=false  # true for managed cloud DB with SSL
ALLOW_SQLITE_FALLBACK=true  # fallback to local SQLite DB when PostgreSQL is unavailable
SQLITE_PATH=./backend/data/frank_media.sqlite

# Notifications (optional channels; fallback logs to server console if not configured)
NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=
ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=
CUSTOMER_NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=
NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_TIMEOUT_MS=7000
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_API_URL=https://api.resend.com/emails
NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_FROM=Frankly Image <notifications@yourdomain.com>
NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_REPLY_TO=
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER=+250000000000
SMS_DEFAULT_COUNTRY_CODE=+250
ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=true
ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_SMS=true
CUSTOMER_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=true
CUSTOMER_NOTIFICATION_SMS=true
ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_EMAILS=owner@yourdomain.com
ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_PHONES=+250000000000
STUDIO_NAME=Frankly Image
SUPPORT_CONTACT=+250-000-000-000
```

### Frontend (.env)

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:4000

# App Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME=Frank Media
VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173
```

### Frontend Production (.env.production)

```env
# Must point to deployed backend
VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.onrender.com

# Or wherever your backend is hosted
VITE_APP_NAME=Frank Media
VITE_APP_URL=https://your-frontend-url.com
```

## Deployment Environment

### Backend Deployment

Set these environment variables in your hosting platform:

| Variable | Value | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `NODE_ENV` | `production` | Enable production mode |
| `PORT` | `4000` | Backend port (auto-assigned by Render) |
| `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | `your_secure_password` | ⚠️ Change from default! |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | From Stripe dashboard | Only if using Stripe |
| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | Your frontend URL | CORS security |
| `PAYMENT_MODE` | `stripe` or `mock` | Use `stripe` for real payments |
| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string | Required for bookings/plans/contact storage |
| `DATABASE_SSL` | `true` or `false` | `true` for cloud databases with SSL |
| `ALLOW_SQLITE_FALLBACK` | `true` | Uses local SQLite DB if PostgreSQL is unavailable (dev only) |
| `SQLITE_PATH` | `./backend/data/frank_media.sqlite` | Local SQLite file path for fallback mode |
| `RESEND_API_KEY` | Resend API key | Enables direct email delivery |
| `NOTIFICATION_EMAIL_FROM` | Sender address | Required for email notifications |
| `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` | Twilio account SID | Enables direct SMS delivery |
| `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN` | Twilio auth token | Required for direct SMS delivery |
| `TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER` | Twilio sender number | Required for direct SMS delivery |
| `ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_EMAILS` | Comma-separated emails | Admin recipients for email alerts |
| `ADMIN_NOTIFICATION_PHONES` | Comma-separated phone numbers | Admin recipients for SMS alerts |

### Frontend Deployment

| Variable | Value | Notes |
|----------|-------|-------|
| `VITE_API_URL` | Your backend URL | e.g., https://frank-media-api.onrender.com |
| `VITE_APP_NAME` | Frank Media | Display name |
| `VITE_APP_URL` | Your frontend URL | For sharing/links |

## Security Checklist

- [ ] Change `ADMIN_PASSWORD` from `admin123` to something secure
- [ ] Set `NODE_ENV=production` on production servers
- [ ] Add `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` with your actual frontend URL
- [ ] Use HTTPS for all URLs (automatic on Render, Vercel, etc.)
- [ ] Set Stripe keys if using real payments
- [ ] Never commit `.env` files with real secrets
- [ ] Rotate passwords regularly
- [ ] Use strong password (min 12 chars with special chars)

## Getting API Keys

### Stripe Setup

1. Go to https://stripe.com
2. Create account and login
3. Navigate to Developers → API Keys
4. Copy Secret Key and Publishable Key
5. Add to `.env` files

### Render Setup

1. Create account at https://render.com
2. Create new Web Service
3. Connect GitHub repository
4. Add environment variables in Settings tab
5. Deploy

## Database Configuration

```env
# PostgreSQL (required)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/frank_media
DATABASE_SSL=false
ALLOW_SQLITE_FALLBACK=true
SQLITE_PATH=./backend/data/frank_media.sqlite
```

Initialize the database schema and seed plans:

```bash
cd backend
npm run db:init
```

## Testing Environment Variables

### Local Testing
```bash
# Backend
cd backend
npm run dev
# Should start on port 4000

# Frontend (new terminal)
cd frontend
npm run dev
# Should start on port 5173
```

### Production Testing
Before deploying, test production build:

```bash
npm run build
npm run preview
```

## Troubleshooting

### API Connection Failed
- Check `VITE_API_URL` is correct
- Ensure backend is running
- Check CORS settings in backend
- Verify `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` includes your frontend

### Admin Login Not Working
- Verify `ADMIN_PASSWORD` is set
- Check password is correct (case-sensitive)
- Clear browser cache
- Try different browser

### Stripe Errors
- Confirm keys are correct
- Ensure payment mode is `stripe` (not `mock`)
- Test with Stripe test cards
- Check publishable key format starts with `pk_`

### Build Errors
- Clear `node_modules` and re-install: `rm -rf node_modules && npm install`
- Check Node.js version: `node --version` (18+ required)
- Check npm cache: `npm cache clean --force`

